{
  "name": "Thruneosaurus Rex",
  "type": "ancestry",
  "effects": [],
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>Developed by Chelaxian diabolists, thruneosauruses are powerful therapods infused with Hell's fury. Few trainers can wrangle such a willful beast, much less check its diabolical urges.</p><p><strong>Size</strong> Large</p><p>Melee <span class=\"pf2-icon\">1</span> jaws, Damage 1d8 piercing Melee <span class=\"pf2-icon\">1</span> foot, Damage 1d8 bludgeoning</p><p><strong>Str</strong> +3, <strong>Dex</strong> +1, <strong>Con</strong> +2, <strong>Int</strong> –3, <strong>Wis</strong> +0, <strong>Cha</strong> +2</p><p><strong>Hit Points</strong> 8</p><p><strong>Skill</strong> Intimidation</p><p><strong>Senses</strong> darkvision, scent (imprecise) 30 feet</p><p><strong>Speed</strong> 35 feet Recessive Fiend A sanctified handler can suppress or fully awaken a thruneosaurus's fiendish influence. Unless you're holy, the dinosaur gains the devil trait. If you're unholy, the dinosaur, its Strikes, and its advanced maneuver gain the unholy trait.</p><p><strong>Support Benefit</strong> Your thruneosaurus's horns radiate heat, igniting distracted foes. Until the start of your next turn, your Strikes that damage a creature in your thruneosaurus's reach also deal 1d6 persistent fire damage. If your thruneosaurus is nimble or savage, the persistent damage increases to 2d6.</p><p><strong>Advanced Maneuver</strong> Hellfire Gaze</p>"
    },
